'''Yevgeny Ivanovich Tolstikov''' ({{lang-ru|Евгений Иванович Толстиков}}) (February 9, 1913 – December 3, 1987) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[polar explorer]], awarded by the [[Hero of the Soviet Union]] title. He led the [[Third Soviet Antarctic Expedition]] and one of the first [[Soviet and Russian manned drifting ice stations|manned drifting ice stations]] in the [[Arctic]].

In 1979, he was made deputy chairman of the [[State Committee for Hydrometeorology and Environmental Control]].

A [[minor planet]] [[3357 Tolstikov]] discovered by Czech astronomer [[Antonín Mrkos]] in 1984 is named after him.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?hl=ru&q=3357+Tolstikov+1984+FT Dictionary of Minor Planet Names – p. 280]</ref>

